    public class FTree

      • resetNodeStates

        @Deprecated
public void resetNodeStates()
        Deprecated. 
        Resets the status of the nodes in the model (e.g. if they have been opened). The effect will be visible only after a call to FContainer.populateView(). This method is primarily meant as a short-term workaround for BUG 11822, and should not be used without a very, very good reason (hence the deprecation).
        See Also:
        NodeState

      • checkAndCorrectPaginationStatusForNode

        public void checkAndCorrectPaginationStatusForNode(java.lang.Object node)
        Reset the paging position to zero, when it's bigger than the number of elements. This can happen when the model changes, e.g. after applying a filter.
        Parameters:
        node - the node to check for its pagination status
